The paper discusses the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories within computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on visual question answering, which involves analyzing images and answering questions about them using both visual and textual information. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
